Three persons have been arrested in Lagos for allegedly gang-raping a minor. The suspects, David Gideon, 21, Sodiq Olayitan, 24, and Mubarak Tajudeen, 23, were said to have abducted, gagged and took turns to rape a 14-year-old girl at Lakeview Estate, Phase Two, Amuwo Odofin. It was learnt that the incident occurred around 5:30pm on February 14 and the boys who committed the crime were four.   Buhari swears-in six new INEC Commissioners     JUST IN: Court orders forfeiture of 10 properties, funds…     BREAKING: Aisha Buhari makes historic visit to Senate…   Police spokesman Adekunle Ajisebutu said efforts were on to arrest the fourth suspect. Ajisebutu said the police moved to the scene as soon as they received information, adding that they recovered a cutlass, dagger, hammer and charms from the suspects. He said the suspects have been transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department (SCID), Panti at the instance of the Commissioner of Police (CP) Abiodun Alabi, for discreet investigation, adding that the victim was rushed to the hospital for treatment.